'''Zidane Ammar Iqbal''' ({{langx|ar|زيدان عمار إقبال}}; born 27 April 2003) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]]. Born in England, he plays for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

Iqbal joined [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]'s youth system aged nine. He made his first-team debut in a [[UEFA Champions League]] match in December 2021. Iqbal represented Iraq at [[Iraq national under-23 football team|under-23]] level before making his senior international debut in January 2022.

==Early life==
Born in [[Manchester]] to a Pakistani father and an Iraqi mother, Iqbal played for local side Sale United from the age of four before joining [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at the age of nine.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-manchester-united-wiki-22406508 |title=Who is Zidane Iqbal? Manchester United teenager profiled after Champions League call-up |website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk |date=8 December 2021 |accessdate=22 February 2022 |archive-date=21 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521193248/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-manchester-united-wiki-22406508 |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Manchester United===
Iqbal signed his first professional contract with [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in April 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-united-transfer-news-contract-20333990|title=Manchester United teenager Zidane Iqbal signs professional contract|first=Samuel|last=Luckhurst|date=7 April 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk|archive-date=27 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127034320/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-united-transfer-news-contract-20333990|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://britasia.tv/sports-pakistani-origin-zidane-iqbal-signs-professional-contract-with-manchester-united/|title=Sports: Pakistani-Origin Zidane Iqbal Signs Professional Contract with Manchester United|first=Priyanca|last=Kumari|date=9 April 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=britasia.tv|archive-date=10 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211210064839/https://britasia.tv/sports-pakistani-origin-zidane-iqbal-signs-professional-contract-with-manchester-united/|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his first-team debut for Manchester United on 8 December 2021 as an 89th-minute substitute in a [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] match against [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Man Utd 1-1 Young Boys: Youthful United side held in final Champions League group game |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59570192 |work=BBC Sport |date=8 December 2021 |accessdate=8 December 2021 |archive-date=12 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211212064605/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59570192 |url-status=live }}</ref> Thus, he became the first British-born South Asian as well the first Iraqi to play for the club, and the first ever British South Asian to play in the Champions League.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Zidane Iqbal becomes Manchester United's first British South Asian player|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59595236|access-date=10 December 2021|date=9 December 2021|work=BBC Sport|last=Varley|first=Ciaran|archive-date=20 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220720102756/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59595236|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12489941/manchester-united-zidane-iqbal-becomes-first-british-south-asian-in-clubs-history-after-champions-league-appearance|title=Zidane Iqbal becomes first British South Asian to play in the UEFA Champions League|website=skysports.com|access-date=6 April 2022|archive-date=31 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531220342/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12489941/manchester-united-zidane-iqbal-becomes-first-british-south-asian-in-clubs-history-after-champions-league-appearance|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Utrecht===
On 23 June 2023, Iqbal announced that he would be leaving Manchester United to join a new club, subject to registration and international clearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/zidane-iqbal-posts-emotional-message-to-club-and-fans-as-man-utd-academy-graduate-departs|title=Iqbal's emotional post as he departs United|first=Adam|last=Bostock|date=23 June 2023|accessdate=26 June 2023|website=ManUtd.com|publisher=Manchester United}}</ref> His move to [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] was announced and finalised on 26 June, on a four-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/zidane-iqbal-permanent-transfer-to-utrecht-from-man-utd-confirmed|title=Iqbal transfer confirmed|first=Adam|last=Marshall|date=26 June 2023|accessdate=26 June 2023|website=ManUtd.com|publisher=Manchester United}}</ref>

==International career==
Iqbal was eligible to represent [[England national football team|England]], [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]], and [[Pakistan national football team|Pakistan]] at international level.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60104894 |title=Zidane Iqbal: Manchester United youngster called up by Iraq |work=BBC Sport |date=23 January 2022 |accessdate=22 February 2022 |archive-date=22 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220222095259/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60104894 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In May 2021, he received an Iraqi passport, and has represented Iraq at youth international level.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shafaq.com/ar/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%80%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8-%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%AF-%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%AC%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%81%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A|title=لاعب مانشستر يونايتد "زيدان إقبال" يتسلم الجواز العراقي|trans-title=Manchester United player Zidane Iqbal receives Iraqi passport|date=20 May 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=shafaq.com|language=Arabic|archive-date=8 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208203849/https://shafaq.com/ar/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%80%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8-%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B1-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%AF-%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%AC%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%81%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="MEN">{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-manchester-united-beckham-21021488|title=Manchester United video suggests Zidane Iqbal may be the next David Beckham in the making|first=Daniel|last=Feliciano|date=10 July 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk|archive-date=20 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220520033650/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-manchester-united-beckham-21021488|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2021, he was called up to the [[Iraq national under-20 football team|Iraq under-20 team]] for the [[2021 Arab Cup U-20]]. However, he was refused to travel by Manchester United, due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ina.iq/127701--.html|title=مانشستر يونايتد يرفض التحاق زيدان بمنتخب الشباب|trans-title=Manchester United refuse Zidane to join the youth team|date=10 June 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=ina.iq|language=Arabic|archive-date=8 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208212849/https://www.ina.iq/127701--.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

In September 2021, Iqbal received his first call up to the [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraq U23]] for a training camp in UAE. He made his debut on 4 September against the [[United Arab Emirates national under-23 football team|UAE U23]], making the starting line-up. In October 2021, Iqbal was named as part of the 23-man Iraq U23 squad for the [[2021 WAFF U-23 Championship]] in Saudi Arabia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ifa.iq/23-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%8B-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%88-7575/|title=3 لاعباً في قائمة منتخبنا الأولمبي لبطولة غرب آسيا|trans-title=Iraqi Olympic team squad|date=1 October 2021|accessdate=2 October 2021|website=Iraq FA|language=Arabic|archive-date=2 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220702135531/https://ifa.iq/23-%d9%84%d8%a7%d8%b9%d8%a8%d8%a7%d9%8b-%d9%81%d9%8a-%d9%82%d8%a7%d8%a6%d9%85%d8%a9-%d9%85%d9%86%d8%aa%d8%ae%d8%a8%d9%86%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a3%d9%88%d9%84%d9%85%d8%a8%d9%8a-%d9%84%d8%a8%d8%b7%d9%88-7575/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 8 October, Iqbal scored his first goal for the Iraq U23 team as the captain of his side.<ref>{{Cite web|date=9 October 2021|title=Zidane Iqbal captains Iraq under-23s and scores|url=https://www.unitedinfocus.com/academy/zidane-iqbal-captains-iraq-under-23s-and-scores/|access-date=8 November 2021|website=United In Focus|archive-date=11 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211111050521/https://www.unitedinfocus.com/academy/zidane-iqbal-captains-iraq-under-23s-and-scores/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Senior ===
In January 2022, Iqbal was called up to the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Iran national football team|Iran]] and [[Lebanon national football team|Lebanon]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Zidane Iqbal: Iraq set to hand Manchester United teenager international debut away in Iran |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12519326/zidane-iqbal-iraq-set-to-hand-manchester-united-teenager-international-debut-away-in-iran |website=Sky Sports |date=20 January 2022 |access-date=24 January 2022 |archive-date=28 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128072334/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12519326/zidane-iqbal-iraq-set-to-hand-manchester-united-teenager-international-debut-away-in-iran |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut in a 1–0 loss to Iran on 27 January 2022.<ref>{{cite web |title=Zidane Iqbal becomes 32nd international player in Manchester United squad |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-manchester-united-internationals-22899229 |website=Manchester Evening News |date=27 January 2022 |access-date=27 January 2022 |archive-date=4 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220204024309/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-manchester-united-internationals-22899229 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 26 March 2024, Iqbal scored his first international goal during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Philippines national football team|Philippines]] in a 5–0 away win.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Web |first=G. C. |date=2024-03-26 |title=Philippines 0-5 Iraq - Philippine Football Federation |url=https://pff.org.ph/philippines-0-5-iraq/ |access-date=2025-08-19 |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Style of play==
{{Expand section|date=March 2026}}
Iqbal is a versatile midfielder who mostly plays in the centre.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zidane Iqbal Positions |url=https://www.footballcritic.com/zidane-iqbal/player-positions/375195 |access-date=2022-10-15 |website=FootballCritic |language=en |archive-date=15 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221015034427/https://www.footballcritic.com/zidane-iqbal/player-positions/375195 |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Personal life==
As one of a large number of [[British Asians in association football]], Iqbal was part of an [[The Football Association|FA]] content series to support South Asian Heritage Month in 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefa.com/news/2021/jul/27/fa-supports-south-asian-heritage-month-20210727|title=A New Content Series will be Released to Support South Asian Heritage Month|date=27 July 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=thefa.com|archive-date=14 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211214042050/https://www.thefa.com/news/2021/jul/27/fa-supports-south-asian-heritage-month-20210727|url-status=live}}</ref>

Iqbal is [[Muslims|Muslim]], and cites [[Mesut Özil]] as an inspiration for him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/zidane-iqbal-interview-with-the-fa-to-mark-south-asian-heritage-month|title=Iqbal Enjoying the 'Rollercoaster Ride'|first=Matthew|last=Holt|date=3 August 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=manutd.com|archive-date=4 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210804155031/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/zidane-iqbal-interview-with-the-fa-to-mark-south-asian-heritage-month|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-man-united-academy-21218237|title=Manchester United academy star Zidane Iqbal names his football idol|first=Liam|last=Wood|date=3 August 2021|accessdate=4 August 2021|website=manchestereveningnews.co.uk|archive-date=21 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521194714/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/zidane-iqbal-man-united-academy-21218237|url-status=live}}</ref> Iqbal has stated in interviews that he is fluent in [[English language|English]] and can speak some [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] and [[Arabic]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 March 2023 |title="They Were All Swinging Their Shoes" 🥴 {{!}} Zidane Iqbal {{!}} Spotlight Questions 💬 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IcrVh7d3X2U=3m41s |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230520232803/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IcrVh7d3X2U=3m41s |archive-date=20 May 2023 |access-date=20 May 2023 |website=YouTube |quote=Event occurs at 3:41}}</ref>

